<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>have the pleasure of someone’s company • take pleasure in someone’s company</xh5><p> <i>have the pleasure of someone’s company</i>—(formal) used when issuing invitations, etc.: May we <u>have the pleasure of your company</u> for lunch tonight?</p><p> <i>take pleasure in someone’s company—</i>enjoy a person’s company: I <u>take pleasure in your company</u>, and do my utmost to give pleasure back to you.</p> </entry>
